<p>When the gateway is started, the thread is also started to make a background monitoring request. The monitoring request makes a while endless loop to poll, and the request will be hijacked on the background side. This is specifically analyzed in the background summary (<a href="https://blog.csdn.net/zm469568595/article/details/113207367" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">后台与网关数据同步 (Http 长轮询篇 &lt;二&gt;)</a>).</p>
<p>The following shows the overall process of monitoring data changes by the gateway:</p>
<figure><img src="/assets/img/blog1/03.png" alt="03" tabindex="0"><figcaption>03</figcaption></figure>
<p>The corresponding actual code implementation is as follows:</p>
<figure><img src="/assets/img/blog1/04.png" alt="04" tabindex="0"><figcaption>04</figcaption></figure>
